description:
Implement the repr() method for JinjaPromptValue - determines how Jinja sees the object (map, seq, or plain).

Location: crates/baml-bridge/src/prompt/jinja.rs

```rust
impl Object for JinjaPromptValue {
    fn repr(self: &Arc<Self>) -> ObjectRepr {
        // Type-first, value-fallback rule
        match &self.pv.ty {
            TypeIR::Class { .. } => ObjectRepr::Map,
            TypeIR::Map(_, _, _) => ObjectRepr::Map,
            TypeIR::List(_, _) => ObjectRepr::Seq,
            _ => {
                // Fallback to value shape if type doesn't specify
                match &self.pv.value {
                    BamlValue::Class(_, _) => ObjectRepr::Map,
                    BamlValue::Map(_) => ObjectRepr::Map,
                    BamlValue::List(_) => ObjectRepr::Seq,
                    _ => ObjectRepr::Plain,
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

This affects:
- ObjectRepr::Map: value.field, iteration over keys
- ObjectRepr::Seq: value[i], iteration over items
- ObjectRepr::Plain: no iteration, no field access

The 'type-first' rule means if TypeIR says it's a Class, treat it as map even if BamlValue doesn't match (rare but possible in schema evolution).
